$\mathrm{H}_2$ and $\mathrm{O}_2$ are produced at cathode and anode respectively. At cathode:
$2 \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{O}+2 \mathrm{e}^{-} \longrightarrow \mathrm{H}_2+2 \mathrm{OH}^{-}$
$2 \mathrm{~F} \quad 1 \mathrm{~mol}$
At anode:
$\begin{array}{r}
2 \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{O} \longrightarrow \mathrm{O}_2+4 \mathrm{H}^{+}+4 \mathrm{e}^{-} \\
\frac{1}{2} \mathrm{~mol} \quad 2 \mathrm{~F}
\end{array}$
$\begin{aligned}
\text { Total volume of gases } & =22.4 \mathrm{~L} \mathrm{H}_2 \\
& \frac{+11.2 \mathrm{~L} \mathrm{O}_2}{33.6 \mathrm{~L}}
\end{aligned}$
